<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="864" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Leishman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis states that the reported audience with the Sultan is
                            gratifying, and that, pending further report promised for Tuesday, <pb facs="0912" n="824" xml:id="pg_824"/> the squadron under the command
                            of Admiral Barker will be held in readiness subject to orders. The
                            Government of the United States expects that its wishes will be fully
                            complied with. Instructs him to keep the Department adequately
                            advised.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>